reviewText: I caught this recently and loved it.  I highly recommend it to anyone that likes good things.  Five Stars .

I caught this by chance on PBS a few months ago and have been wanting to get a copy for myself ever since. If you love a good story about Chicago History then look no further.

Recommended for fans of: Jaws, Back to the Future, Jurassic Park, 2001: A Space Odyssey, The Shining, Dumb and Dumber, Every movie ever made.

Maybe my fault for not realizing that this was NOT a movie but a documentary.  If you are big on history perhaps you would enjoy, but if you are looking for a love story acted out, this isn't it.  Had I been a little less anxious to place an order I may have realized that there are no actors listed.  Since I often buy British films the actors are not always known to me and I have apparently become careless in my reviews.  I found the editors remarks to be misleading also, although it is pointed out that they were in love, it could hardly be a love story.
Very interesting but this is a documentary not a movie.
Fascinating woman.  this is a great story, great Chicago History.
I'm from Chicago and found the history of this staple in my town heartwarming.  It's brief, to the point and full of facts that I found amazing.
Whether you are a Chicago history buff or a historical romance buff you'll find this to be a really nice story. Well told and engaging. And wants you to research more!
Saw this soon after it was available.  It was very well done and anyone who loves Chicago history will enjoy this documentary.
